During the COP26 summit in Glasgow, President Joe Biden emphasized the importance of making sustainable choices in infrastructure development. He highlighted that every decision made in the next decade should bring us closer to achieving net-zero emissions by 2050. Biden discussed the Build Back Better World initiative, which aims to deliver high-quality, sustainable infrastructure in collaboration with G7 partners. He emphasized the need for climate resilience in all projects and the importance of involving local communities in the decision-making process. Biden also stressed the significance of transparency, high standards, and partnerships in infrastructure investments. Lastly, he highlighted the potential of climate infrastructure to drive sustainable economic recovery and create millions of new jobs worldwide.